Debug trait: https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/fmt/trait.Debug.html

It contains ```impl<Ret> Debug for fn() -> Ret```.

I tried to compile this code

https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=360a19def222bb4e64a79dfbe4f2d905&version=stable&backtrace=0
```rust
use std::fmt::Debug;

fn test_debug<T: Debug>(t: T) {}

fn static_fn() {}
fn static_fn_ret() -> (i32) {
    unimplemented!()
}

fn main() {
    test_debug(static_fn);
    test_debug(static_fn_ret);

    let as_var: fn() -> () = static_fn;
    test_debug(as_var);

    fn static_local_fn() {}
    test_debug(static_local_fn);
}
```
I expected it to be compiled, but compiler says Debug is not implemented.


(once per fn, but **except as_var**)
```
test_debug(static_fn);
^^^^^^^^^^ the trait `std::fmt::Debug` is not implemented for `fn() {main::static_local_fn}`
```




